{
  "name": "Snow Sports",
  "overview": "Skiing and snowboarding are the fastest and most thrilling ways to travel on foot in snow country. These sports also provide the physical benefits of fresh air, rhythmic action, and strenuous exercise. Many games and contests give snow sports variety and added rewards.",
  "is_eagle_required": false,
  "is_lab": false,
  "url": "https://www.scouting.org/merit-badges/snow-sports/",
  "pdf_url": "https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Snow%20Sports.pdf",
  "workbook_pdf_url": "http://usscouts.org/mb/worksheets/Snow-Sports.pdf",
  "workbook_docx_url": "http://usscouts.org/mb/worksheets/Snow-Sports.docx",
  "shop_url": "https://www.scoutshop.org/mbp-snow-sports-656882.html",
  "image_url": "https://www.scouting.org/wp-content/uploads/elementor/thumbs/SnowSports-qjjk7p7ex1rmni5l9zqta1xnjo0npalz3uxtbivwps.png",
  "image_filename": "snow-sports-merit-badge.jpg",
  "requirements": [
    {
      "id": "15947",
      "label": "1",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Do the following:"
        }
      ],
      "resources": [],
      "sub_requirements": [
        {
          "id": "15948",
          "label": "a",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Explain to your counselor the hazards you are most likely to encounter while participating in snow sport activities, and what you should do to anticipate, help prevent, mitigate, and respond to these hazards."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "How to Ski Safely (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/AKxY8Xm-Gg0?si=EK3y5wxrfgJTmAk9"
            },
            {
              "title": "How to Prevent Injuries (website)",
              "url": "https://centerforspineandortho.com/common-skiing-and-snowboarding-injuries-and-how-to-prevent-them/%20"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "15949",
          "label": "b",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Discuss first aid and prevention for the types of injuries or illnesses that could occur while participating in snow sports, including hypothermia, frostbite, shock, dehydration, sunburn, concussion, fractures, bruises, sprains, and strains. Tell how to apply splints."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "Treating Frostbite and Hypothermia (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/tHiav9zYJT0?si=VC-plNy5tA2XSZ1I"
            },
            {
              "title": "How to Splint a Broken Bone (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/jo2zi_JB9_4?si=nVI-3TY16Ma1BL1p"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "15950",
      "label": "2",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Do the following:"
        }
      ],
      "resources": [],
      "sub_requirements": [
        {
          "id": "15951",
          "label": "a",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Explain why every snow sport participant should be prepared to render first aid in the event of an accident."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "15952",
          "label": "b",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Explain the procedure used to report an accident to the local ski patrol or local emergency personnel."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "How to Report an Accident to the Ski Patrol (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/Zl0ZyNoox8M?si=xgYuHNUn5izc4HA7"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "16005",
      "label": "3",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Explain the international trail-marking system."
        }
      ],
      "resources": [
        {
          "title": "International Trail Marking System (video)",
          "url": "https://youtu.be/N_f6xMFVVHc"
        }
      ],
      "sub_requirements": []
    },
    {
      "id": "16006",
      "label": "4",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Discuss the importance of strength, endurance, and flexibility in snow sports. Demonstrate exercises and activities you can do to get fit for the option you choose in requirement 7."
        }
      ],
      "resources": [
        {
          "title": "Training to Prevent Snow Sports Injuries (video)",
          "url": "https://youtu.be/a8sf5k3fH9I"
        }
      ],
      "sub_requirements": []
    },
    {
      "id": "16007",
      "label": "5",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Present yourself properly clothed and equipped for the option you choose in requirement 7. Discuss how the clothing you have chosen will help keep you warm and protected."
        }
      ],
      "resources": [
        {
          "title": "How to Dress for Snow Sports (video)",
          "url": "https://youtu.be/mjJNpR3nepM"
        }
      ],
      "sub_requirements": []
    },
    {
      "id": "15953",
      "label": "6",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Do ALL of the following:"
        }
      ],
      "resources": [],
      "sub_requirements": [
        {
          "id": "15954",
          "label": "a",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Explain the elements of the "
            },
            {
              "type": "element",
              "tag": "i",
              "attrs": {},
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "Your Responsibility Code"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " that is in effect at the location whehre you will ski, snowboard, or snowshoe. Explain why each person must follow this code."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "Your Responsibility Code (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/euGO92z4MnM"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "15955",
          "label": "b",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Explain the "
            },
            {
              "type": "element",
              "tag": "i",
              "attrs": {},
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "SMART Style"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " safety program. Tell why it is important and how it applies to participants at snow sport venues like terrain parks and pipes."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "SMART Style Safety Program (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/4Y7lCN7SKiY"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "15956",
          "label": "c",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Explain the precautions pertaining to avalanche safety, including the responsibility of individuals regarding avalanche safety."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "How to Reduce Avalanche Risk (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/_f-vEc5LTFM"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "15957",
      "label": "7",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Do ONE of the following options:"
        }
      ],
      "resources": [],
      "sub_requirements": [
        {
          "id": "15958",
          "label": null,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "element",
              "tag": "strong",
              "attrs": {},
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "Option A—Downhill (Alpine) Skiing."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " Do ALL of the following: "
            },
            {
              "type": "element",
              "tag": "br",
              "attrs": {},
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "type": "element",
              "tag": "br",
              "attrs": {},
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "type": "element",
              "tag": "b",
              "attrs": {},
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "Note:"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " Generally, a gentle slope will be a trail designated by a green circle, a slightly steeper slope will be a green circle or blue square trail, and an intermediate slope will be a blue square trail. However, your counselor should determine what type of hill is most suited to your skill level and allows you to demonstrate each of the required skills."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "15959",
          "label": "1",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Show how to wax and maintain your skis and use/maintain your release bindings. Explain the international DIN standard and what it means to skiers."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "How to Wax Skis (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/1Xt1gZfZ2Rw"
            },
            {
              "title": "How to Test Ski Bindings (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/Ix27SNEsRYM"
            },
            {
              "title": "Ski Binding DIN Settings (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/DkNAXgc2-rk?si=p-0U6YH1kIngZ47t"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "15960",
          "label": "2",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Explain the American Teaching System and a basic snowskiing progression."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "American Teaching System Skill Levels (PDF)",
              "url": "https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Snow%20Sports/american_teaching_system_levels.pdf"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "15961",
          "label": "3",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Discuss the different types of Alpine skis. Demonstrate two ways to carry skis and poles safely and easily."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "Types of Alpine Skis (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/PXR5vRgIlJE"
            },
            {
              "title": "How to Carry Skis (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/GLu49jDy51k"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "15962",
          "label": "4",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Demonstrate how to ride one kind of lift and explain how to ride two others."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "Ski Lifts and How to Ride Them (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/4xkGmEC-vPk"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "15963",
          "label": "5",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "On a gentle slope, demonstrate some of the beginning maneuvers learned in skiing. Include the straight run, gliding wedge, wedge stop, sidestep, and herringbone maneuvers."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "Beginner's Guide - The Gear (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/LaF1tT1l7c0?si=A4krxuBaIP1wPGgx"
            },
            {
              "title": "Beginner's Guide - Basic Moves (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/l6AG5WLUaNo?si=Cy7fDWXKwAFsQp9B"
            },
            {
              "title": "Beginner's Guide - Getting Around (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/zAQVuC1Q4mw?si=ofT18Us8eaEUr9_w"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "15964",
          "label": "6",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "On slightly steeper terrain, show linked wedge turns."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "How to Do Linked Wedge Turns (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/1BdMf9rmubQ"
            },
            {
              "title": "The Wedge Turn (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/9bEH6JCq83U?si=5ru69RVAgDgQfAif"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "15965",
          "label": "7",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "On a moderate slope, demonstrate five to 10 christies."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "How to Do Christies (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/x5q0yV14sas"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "15966",
          "label": "8",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Make a controlled run down an intermediate slope."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "Making a Controlled Run (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/CMgId4iSlcE"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "15967",
          "label": "9",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Demonstrate the ability to ski in varied conditions, including changes in pitch and snow conditions. Maintain your balance and ability to turn."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "Skiing in Variable Snow Conditions (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/DQv53VSxykY?si=wBlVELSoFcvQ973i"
            }
          ],
          "sub_requirements": []
        },
        {
          "id": "15968",
          "label": "10",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Name the major ski organizations in the United States and explain their functions."
            }
          ],
          "resources": [
            {
              "title": "Professional Ski Instructors of America (PSIA) (video)",
              "url": "https://youtu.be/Z_Jh5pfseU8"
